  • Incident Date: 2025-02-06
  • City: ALEXANDRIA
  • State: IN
  • Report Type: A hazardous material incident
  • Mode Of Transportation: Highway
  • Carrier/Reporter: LANDSTAR INWAY, INC.
  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Total Amount Of Damages: 6000
  • Serious Incident Ind: No
  • Description: On February 11, 2025, at 1540 ET, Landstar Inway personnel contacted ERTS regarding the presence of residue of a sodium hydroxide solution released from a plastic tote, impacting the trailer floor only. Contractors were dispatched to clean up the release using absorbents and the proper PPE. Contractors used a citric acid solution to neutralize the area before confirming with pH testing. All waste was containerized in one (1) 55-gal poly drum which was transported offsite by contractors pending disposal.

item.description:

  • Incident Date: 2025-01-23
  • City: LOWELL
  • State: IN
  • Report Type: A hazardous material incident
  • Mode Of Transportation: Highway
  • Carrier/Reporter: DAYTON FREIGHT LINES, INC.
  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Total Amount Of Damages: 0
  • Serious Incident Ind: No
  • Description: Dayton Freight personnel observed approximately one (1) gallon of material released from one (1) 1-gallon metal pails due to improperly loaded freight that resulted in the pail leaking. The released material impacted the trailer floor and three other pails. Dayton Freight personnel deployed absorbents to the impacted area and gathered the spent material and containerized it into one (1) 5-gallon metal drum. Another one (1) 5-gallon metal drum was also used to contain the impacted pails. The generated waste was staged onsite at the terminal in a secure location. The generated waste will remain onsite for Dayton Freightâ€™s contracted hazardous waste vendor to coordinate disposal.

item.title: Report I-2025010016
item.description:
Report I-2025010016

Identified by scraper @ 2025-02-13T06:18:15+00:00

  • Incident Date: 2024-12-16
  • City: INDIANAPOLIS
  • State: IN
  • Report Type: A hazardous material incident
  • Mode Of Transportation: Highway
  • Carrier/Reporter: HERITAGE TRANSPORT, LLC
  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Total Amount Of Damages: 0
  • Serious Incident Ind: No
  • Description: Material leaked out of the bottom of the roll off box. Material was not fully dumped from this roll off box and doesn't appear to be lined. With the rainfall and open tarp, rain water started accumulating inside the box and combined with the heel of waste inside the box. This leaked all down the side of the of 2 other roll off boxes. Those boxes were moved to get to the leaking box. Floor dry was placed in all areas where waste was located and booms were put to contain the spill.
